{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JrDSgC7yV2vCMGxuv5zfUp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015bpMbAUJQHdb8EcBhdS8Ng","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A cell containing =SUM(A1:A10) evaluates to the correct sum of values in cells A1 through A10","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Testing SUM in isolation with mocked cell values would miss failures in how the engine resolves range references (A1:A10) and integrates cell lookup with formula evaluation. A real failure requires wiring together the range parser, cell resolver, and evaluator with actual cell objects. Mocking cell lookup hides bugs in reference resolution, type coercion, and cascading updates.","test_description":"Create a sheet with cells A1–A10 populated with numeric values (1, 2, ..., 10), add a cell with formula =SUM(A1:A10), evaluate the sheet, and assert result is 55. Test with floating-point values, mixed numeric types, and edge cases (zeros, negatives) to catch precision and coercion bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test requires multiple modules (sheet, cell objects, parser, evaluator) wired together, not just function logic.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A cell referencing another cell that contains a formula produces the correct cascaded result","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Mocking cell B1's result would hide bugs in how the engine tracks and resolves formula-to-formula dependencies and evaluation order. The real failure is 'when B1 depends on A1, and C1 depends on B1, does C1 get the correct value?' This requires multiple cell objects wired together and proper dependency resolution.","test_description":"Create A1=5, B1=A1*2, C1=B1+1. Evaluate C1 and verify result is 11. Change A1 to 10 and verify C1 updates to 2