ively in a single pass. Test with deeper graphs and multiple independent branches.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test requires full sheet with dependency tracking and observing recalculation order.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"The undo operation after editing a formula restores both the formula text and all previously computed dependent values","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Testing the undo mechanism on a command history structure is unit-testable, but the real failure is when undo doesn't restore both the original formula text AND all previously computed values. Mocking cell state hides bugs in snapshot restoration or selective state rollback.","test_description":"Create A1=5, B1=A1*2 (=10), C1=B1+1 (=11). Edit B1 to A1*3, triggering recalculation (B1→15, C1→16). Call undo and verify B1's formula reverts to \"=A1*2\" and C1 recomputes to 11. Test multi-step undo and alternating edit/undo sequences.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test requires editor, evaluator, and undo system integration with observation of both formula and computed state.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Saving a workbook to disk and loading it back produces identical cell values and formulas with no data loss or floating-point precision change","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This explicitly requires file I/O and persistence. Mocking the file system hides serialization bugs (incorrect binary encoding, floating-point precision loss, formula corruption) or file write/read errors. Real failures include data loss on disk, encoding mismatches, or precision loss in floating-point round-tripping. System-level file I/O is the minimum.","test_description":"Create a workbook with mixed types: integers, floating-point (e.g., 0.1+0.2), text, formula